        <div id="comment_body_36398928" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>I wonder... is the conversion rate dropping because people are smarter, or because the sheer amount of spam has risen?</p><p>It would seem that they'd saturated the fundamental market (stupid people) pretty quickly.  You can send the stupid people more offers, but even the stupid people are only going to buy so much stuff.</p><p>If they'd reached 90% of the stupid people with the first billion emails they sent out, they'd probably have to send 10 billion emails to reach 99% of the stupid people: a 10x rise in spam for a 10% improvement in the market size.</p><p>Or maybe it's just a diminishing number of stupid people.  That would be a nice thought.</p></div>
