<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_36401462" data-cid="36401462">
    <div id="comment_36401462">
        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Does anyone here actually get spam email?"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Does anyone here actually get spam email?<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~yarnosh" class="author" title="author name and user ID">yarnosh (2055818) </a> | more than 3 years ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2227792&cid=36401462">(#36401462)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_36401462" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">Seriously, who still gets spam email these days? Filtering solutions are fairly mature and effective. I might go so far as to say we're winning the battle... if it weren't for the fact that like 90% of all email is spam. Still, I publish my gmail address all over the feakin' place including usenet and I can't remember the last time I got a single piece of spam in my inbox or a missed email due to filtering. When I ran my own mail server I could filter out most spam as well using free tools and techiques. So, what's the big deal? Who is still getting spam and why haven't you changed email providers?</div>
